    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T07:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T07:30:00-05:00" n="1229"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1229">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/7–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1229<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Japanese Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_TS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Togo</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Japanese Ambassador in the Soviet
                        Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SN1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sato</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21T21:30:00+09:00"
                            >July 21, 1945—9:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>931. Re your telegrams No. 1417 and No. 1418.<note n="1" xml:id="d1229fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1226">Documents Nos. 1226</ref> and <ref target="#d1227"
                            >1227</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The mission of special envoy <persName corresp="#p_KPF1">Konoye</persName> is to
                    ask the Government of the USSR for its assistance in terminating the <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss> and to explain our concrete intentions
                    concerning the matter in accordance with the wishes of the Emperor; it is also
                    to negotiate on matters of establishing cooperative relations between Japan and
                    the USSR, which should become basic in our diplomacy during and after the <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Please propose the above to the Soviets and endeavor to obtain the agreement of
                    the Government of the USSR relative to the dispatch of the special envoy.</p>
                <p>Also, please understand fully my telegram No. 932<note n="2" xml:id="d1229fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1230">Document No. 1230</ref>.</note> in particular.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
